workflow.name: GPT 4.1 - Freelancer.com job alert system with auto proposal generator
workflow.description:
**Be first. Be relevant. Get hired.**  
This ready-to-import **n8n workflow** automates your entire Freelancer.com job search:  
it **scans new listings**, **filters the best ones with AI**, **writes proposal drafts**, and **sends them to Telegram instantly** ‚Äî all while **logging every opportunity** into Google Sheets.

---

## üí° Why Freelancers Love It

- ‚ö° **Instant Alerts:** Get notified within minutes of new high-quality jobs.  
- üß† **AI-Powered Scoring:** Filters scams, vague clients, and low-value gigs automatically.  
- ‚úçÔ∏è **Smart Proposal Drafts:** GPT-4.1 crafts 150‚Äì200 word personalized proposals for you.  
- üì± **Telegram Integration:** See job details + AI proposal in one alert message.  
- üìä **Auto Tracking:** Logs every lead in Google Sheets with scores, notes, and timestamps.  

**Spend less time searching ‚Äî and more time winning projects.**

---

## üß© What‚Äôs Included

- ‚úÖ **n8n Workflow (.json)** ‚Äî ready to import and launch  
- ‚úÖ **Setup Guide (Markdown)** ‚Äî complete 5-step configuration walkthrough  
 

---

## üß∞ Requirements

- Free **n8n Cloud** account (or self-hosted instance)  
- **OpenAI API key** (GPT-4.1 or GPT-4-mini)  
- **Telegram bot** + Chat ID (takes 2 minutes to create)  
- **Google Sheets** account  

---

## ü™ú 5-Step Setup Guide (Detailed)

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Prepare Your Tools
- Get your **OpenAI key** ‚Üí [platform.openai.com](https://platform.openai.com)  
- Create a **Telegram bot** via **@BotFather** ‚Üí copy your token  
- Use **@userinfobot** to get your **Chat ID**  
- Create a **Google Sheet** with headers:  
  `Timestamp | Job | Description | Link | AI Score | Reasoning | Red Flags | Client Type | AI Proposal | Alert Timestamp`  
- Keep all keys and URLs ready.

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Import the Workflow in n8n
- Open n8n ‚Üí **+ Workflow ‚Üí Import from File** ‚Üí choose the `.json` provided below.  
- Once imported, open these nodes and connect your credentials:
  - **OpenAI nodes** ‚Üí add your API key  
  - **Google Sheets nodes** ‚Üí sign in with Google  
  - **Telegram node** ‚Üí paste your bot token + chat ID  
- Confirm the **Schedule Trigger** runs every **5 minutes** (default).  

---

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Personalize Your Keywords & Filters
- Open **Settings (Keyword & Wishlist)**:
  - `Job Keyword`: e.g., `react`, `seo`, `logo design`, `automation`
  - `Wishlist`: e.g., `Budget > $500, clear brief, long-term clients`
- The RSS node auto-fetches new jobs from Freelancer.com:
  ```
  https://www.freelancer.com/rss.xml?keyword={{$json['Job Keyword']}}
  ```
  Optional filters:  
  - `&min_price=500` ‚Üí only projects $500+  
  - `&max_price=5000` ‚Üí skip mega-projects  
- Adjust **Filter Job Quality**:
  - Description > 100 chars  
  - Posted within the last 2 hours  
- Tune **AI Score Threshold (Gate Node)** to `>= 7` for balanced alerts.

---

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Test Your Automation
- Click **Execute Workflow** once.
- If everything is set:
  - üü¢ Nodes turn green (success)
  - üì© Telegram shows your first job alert
  - üìä Google Sheet updates with a new job entry
- If empty, try:
  - Broader keyword (e.g., `python` instead of `python scraper`)
  - Increase freshness (2 ‚Üí 6 hours)

---

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Go Live & Expand
- Activate your workflow.
- Let it run for 24‚Äì48 hours, then refine:
  - Raise **score threshold** to 8‚Äì9 for higher quality
  - Add **RSS nodes** for new categories (design, dev, content)
  - Extend alerts to **Slack, Discord, or Email**
  - Replace Google Sheets with **Airtable** or **Notion**
- **Pro Tip:** Use **Apify** to scrape Upwork, Fiverr, or niche job boards ‚Üí feed results into the same analyzer chain.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è How It Works (Behind the Scenes)

```
Schedule ‚Üí Fetch RSS ‚Üí Filter ‚Üí AI Analyze (score 1‚Äì10)
        ‚Üí If score ‚â• 7 ‚Üí AI Proposal ‚Üí Log to Sheets ‚Üí Send Telegram Alert
```

You still review and apply manually (TOS-safe), but you‚Äôll always be among the **first 5 applicants**.

---



## üîå Future-Proof Extensions

| Extension | Description |
|------------|--------------|
| **Apify Integration** | Scrape Upwork, Fiverr, or niche boards with structured data |
| **Multi-Channel Alerts** | Add Slack, Discord, or email digests |
| **Team Routing** | Send design jobs to one chat, dev jobs to another |
| **Advanced Scoring** | Add client history or location weighting |
| **Database Sync** | Replace Sheets with Notion, Airtable, or PostgreSQL |



## üßæ Terms & Notes

- Manual review required (no auto-apply)  
- API costs: OpenAI ~$5‚Äì10/month  
- Respects Freelancer.com Terms of Service  
- All keys stored securely inside n8n credentials  

---

## üèÅ Summary

**Automate your freelancing workflow.**  
This system finds, filters, and drafts proposals for you while you sleep.  
‚öôÔ∏è Plug it into n8n ‚Üí üîë Add keys ‚Üí üéØ Go live ‚Üí üí∞ Start winning faster.

nodes.name: Fetch Freelancer.com RSS
nodes.notes:
üåê RSS FETCH ‚Äî Setup
Fetches the latest jobs from Freelancer.com.

CUSTOMIZE URL:
‚Ä¢ ?keyword=wordpress
‚Ä¢ &min_price=500
‚Ä¢ &max_price=5000

Example:
https://www.freelancer.com/rss.xml?keyword=wordpress&min_price=500

üí° Use multiple RSS nodes for multiple keywords.

nodes.name: Filter Job Quality
nodes.notes:
‚úÖ QUALITY FILTER ‚Äî Customize
Current rules:
‚Ä¢ Description > 100 chars
‚Ä¢ Posted within last 2 hours

OPTIONAL:
‚Ä¢ Budget thresholds (if present in feed)
‚Ä¢ Required/excluded keywords

TIP: Start loose, tighten after 1‚Äì2 days.

nodes.name: AI Job Analyzer
nodes.notes:
üß† AI ANALYZER ‚Äî Setup
Scores the job 1‚Äì10, explains reasoning, flags risks, and classifies client type.

TIP: Keep wishlist specific to reduce noise.

nodes.name: Structured Output Parser
nodes.notes:
üß© OUTPUT PARSER ‚Äî Stability
Forces strict JSON so downstream filters/logging never break.

nodes.name: AI Proposal Generator
nodes.notes:
‚úçÔ∏è PROPOSAL WRITER ‚Äî Customize
Edit "My Skills" / "My Experience" and drop one relevant portfolio link.

üí° 90% done by AI ‚Üí add 10% personal touch.

nodes.name: Log to Google Sheets
nodes.notes:
üìä JOB LOGGER ‚Äî Setup
Append/Update by Link to avoid duplicates.

Recommended columns: Timestamp | Job | Description | Link | AI Score | Reasoning | Red Flags | Client Type | AI Proposal | Alert Timestamp.

nodes.name: Send Telegram Alert
nodes.notes:
üì± TELEGRAM ‚Äî Setup
Create bot with @BotFather ‚Üí add token in credentials ‚Üí DM your bot ‚Üí get Chat ID via @userinfobot and paste here.

TIP: Add buttons via your own webhook for Skip / Applied.

nodes.name: Schedule: Every 5 Minutes1
nodes.notes:
‚è∞ TRIGGER ‚Äî Schedule
Runs this workflow every 5 minutes.

‚úèÔ∏è CUSTOMIZE:
‚Ä¢ 3 min = ultra-competitive niches
‚Ä¢ 10‚Äì15 min = lower API cost

üí° TIP: Start at 5 min and tune after 1‚Äì2 days based on alert volume.

nodes.name: Settings (Keyword & Wishlist)1
nodes.notes:
‚öôÔ∏è SETTINGS ‚Äî Setup
Define your main keyword and your "wish list" criteria.

Examples:
‚Ä¢ Job Keyword: shopify, react, seo
‚Ä¢ Wishlist: "Budget > $500, clear scope, no vague fixed-price"

üí° TIP: Clone this node to run multiple keywords in parallel (merge later).

nodes.name: Load Seen Links (Google Sheets)1
nodes.notes:
üì• DEDUPE SOURCE ‚Äî Setup
Loads previously processed links from your tracking sheet.

SETUP:
‚Ä¢ Use the same spreadsheet as the logger
‚Ä¢ Column "Link" must exist

üîí Prevents duplicate alerts.

nodes.name: Collect Seen Links1
nodes.notes:
üßÆ AGGREGATE ‚Äî Setup
Builds a quick lookup of already seen links for the dedupe filter.

nodes.name: De-duplicate by Link1
nodes.notes:
üö´ DEDUPE ‚Äî Customize
Only pass jobs whose link is not already in your sheet.

TIP: If your source has unstable links, switch to a hash of (title+date).

nodes.name: LLM (OpenAI)1
nodes.notes:
‚öôÔ∏è LLM BACKEND ‚Äî Setup
Used by Analyzer & Proposal nodes.

TIP: Use gpt-4o-mini for speed/cost unless you need richer reasoning.

nodes.name: Gate: Score ‚â•
nodes.notes:
üéØ SCORE GATE ‚Äî Customize
Only pass jobs with score ‚â• 7.

6 = more alerts, 8 = only premium.

nodes.name: CV (Sheets Tool)1
nodes.notes:
üõ†Ô∏è SHEETS TOOL ‚Äî Optional
For advanced automations (e.g., pulling portfolio snippets). Safe to disable initially.

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.

data.details: The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
